{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5e829cff-65d8-411a-b94d-3fbe684e199f","content":"This is an **MSTest 3.8.0** project running on **Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP)** — indicated by `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport=true` in `Directory.Build.props` and the `MSTest` 3.8.0 meta-package which enables the MTP runner.\n\nLet me run the integration tests filtered by `TestCategory=Integration`:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01G3vpfD3Sp53azNPbK1VupJ","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Running integration tests"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01QDGL5w8XQTeMDc5aMf8ffj","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-ad57023578264aab9ce160232495dad5 && dotnet test --filter \"TestCategory=Integration\" 2>&1","description":"Run integration tests with dotnet test","initial_wait":60},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Run integration tests with dotnet test"}],"interactionId":"b59dd753-3d4f-4b45-9253-efe739b2108a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me analyze the project:\n\n1. **Framework**: MSTest 3.8.0\n2. **Platform**: Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) — indicated by `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true` in Directory.Build.props and MSTest 3.8.0 which includes `EnableMSTestRunner` by default (actually, looking more carefully, MSTest 3.x with `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` uses VSTest by default, but `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enables MTP support via `dotnet test`).\n\nWait, let me reconsider. MSTest 3.8.0 with the `MSTest` meta-package includes `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter`. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property in Directory.Build.props enables Microsoft.Testing.Platform support through `dotnet test`.\n\n\nActually, with MSTest 3.x, the `MSTest` meta-package (starting from 3.2) consolidates the framework, adapter, and analyzers together. The `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` provides the VSTest infrastructure, while `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` bridges `dotnet test` to MTP.\n\nSo this setup is MSTest 3.8.0 running on Microsoft.Testing.Platform. For filtering by category with MTP, the syntax differs from VSTest—I need to check whether `dotnet test` translates the traditional VSTest-style filters or if it requires MTP-specific filter syntax.","outputTokens":876,"requestId":"4C1F:1FB596:CB1A55:F9D22C:6A013306"},"id":"3d782390-3f72-4c6c-8334-f45e8814a538","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:38:31.767Z","parentId":"7720db50-1c85-4fac-b049-b7d5d60722a1"}
